
command1 || command2 
command2 is executed if, and only if, command1 returns a non-zero exit status. 
In other words, run command1 successfully or run command2.


command1 && command2
command2 is executed if, and only if, command1 returns an exit status of zero (true).
In other words, run command1 and if it is successfull, then run command2
